<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430733>
    dc:description "FIGURES 62–73. (62–65). Maladera rufocuprea (Blanchard, 1850) (Bankura, West Bengal); (66–69). Maladera schenklingi (Moser, 1918) (Purnea, Bihar); (70–73). Maladera setosa (Brenske, 1896) (West Champaran, Bihar); (62, 66, 70) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (63, 67, 71) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (64, 68, 72) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (65, 69, 73) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430733/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430757>
    dc:description "FIGURE 100. (A–B). A. Gangetic plains biogeographic zone of India; B. Map of Lower Gangetic plains showing sample localities of the species: Maladera proxima, M. reyaensis, M. rufocuprea, M. schenklingi, M.setosa, M. siniaevi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430757/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

